      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STARVERNA (4) three-year-old Star Turn filly from Tennessee Diamond on debut for the Lou Mary yard. Has shown enough in her three trials to suggest she can get the job done on debut. BUNDORAN (1) comes here with a fitness edge over most of these in a winnable race. Covered ground from the wide gate with a game fourth over 1000m at Tamworth. Stalks the speed and is among the better hopes. NULKABA STAR (7) has been average in three runs back and the senior rider goes on today. Tried hard with the 59kg when fifth over 1100m at Scone. Well placed with the 55.5kg and stays in the mix. MOONLIGHT ODYSSEY (3) nor that far away on resumption with an eye catching fifth over 900m at this track. Fitter now and doesn't have to improve much to take a hand in the finish.",
